50%2C000%20hours.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20probably%20saw%20all%20of%20these%20movies.%20But%20were%20you%20waiting%20in%20anticipation%20to%20see%20them%20on%20the%20streamer%2C%20or%20did%20you%20stumble%20across%20them%20once%20they%20were%20already%20on%20the%20service%3F%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChances%20are%2C%20it%20was%20the%20latter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%229000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Millie%20Bobby%20Brown%20in%20Damsel%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e8b0636080194819fd2357%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMillie%20Bobby%20Brown%20in%20%26quot%3BDamsel.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EJohn%20Wilson%2FNetflix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20top%20three%20titles%20have%20in%20common%20is%20that%20they%20all%20were%20released%20by%20Netflix%20with%20little%20to%20no%20publicity%20or%20marketing%20fanfare.%20While%20that%20might%20come%20as%20a%20shock%2C%20the%20streaming%20giant%20has%20been%20using%20this%20strategy%20since%20it%20began%20making%20original%20content%2C%20especially%20movies%2C%20back%20in%20the%202010s.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClearly%2C%20this%20new%20data%20proves%20the%20strategy%20is%20working.%20The%20Netflix%20homepage%20has%20essentially%20become%20its%20own%20watercooler%20destination%2C%20directing%20users%20to%20the%20hottest%20titles%20on%20its%20Top%2010%20list%20and%20putting%20its%20newest%20releases%20in%20splashy%20top%20banners%2C%20encouraging%20users%20to%20push%20play%20first%2C%20ask%20questions%20later.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20robust%20landing%20page%20has%20allowed%20Netflix%20to%20eschew%20spending%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20promoting%20many%20of%20its%20original%20films.%20If%20audiences%20will%20find%20them%20on%20the%20app%20anyway%2C%20why%20bother%20building%20pre-release%20hype%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20that's%20not%20the%20strategy%20for%20every%20single%20Netflix%20Original.%20Eddie%20Murphy%20returning%20to%20one%20of%20his%20most%20beloved%20franchises%20with%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeverly-hills-cop-axel-f-stunts-real-not-cgi-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBeverly%20Hills%20Cop%3A%20Axel%20F%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20rightfully%20put%20Netflix's%20marketing%20department%20in%20overdrive%3A%20there%20was%20a%20splashy%20premiere%20in%20Beverly%20Hills%2C%20and%20huge%20billboards%20featuring%20Murphy%20in%20his%20character's%20iconic%20Detroit%20Lions%20jacket%20spread%20for%20miles%20on%20Sunset%20Boulevard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%26quot%3BSociety%20of%20the%20Snow%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Spanish-language%20true%20story%20about%20a%20rugby%20team%20stranded%20in%20the%20Andes%20after%20their%20plane%20crashes%2C%20got%20next%20to%20nothing%20in%20terms%20of%20promotion%20from%20Netflix%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20%3Cem%3Estill%3C%2Fem%3E%20came%20out%20in%20the%20top%20three.%20(The%20movie%20did%2C%20however%2C%20land%20a%20best%20foreign%20film%20Oscar%20nomination%2C%20which%20may%20have%20helped%20its%20exposure%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20certainly%20did%20not%20get%20billboards%20on%20Sunset%20Boulevard.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Agust%C3%ADn%20Pardella%20as%20Nando%20Parrado%20and%20Mat%C3%ADas%20Recalt%20as%20Roberto%20Canessa%20in%20Netflix's%20%26quot%3BSociety%20of%20the%20Snow.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6597ec776979d7371820aedf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222001%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BSociety%20of%20the%20Snow.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EQuim%20Vives%2FNetflix%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20strategy%20that's%20left%20most%20of%20Hollywood%20still%20scratching%20its%20head.%20The%20logic%20goes%20that%20because%20Netflix%20wants%20to%20be%20a%20destination%2C%20it%20doesn't%20need%20major%20promotion%2C%20or%20even%20its%20movies%20in%20theaters%20first%20in%20order%20to%20get%20eyeballs%20(unless%20the%20big-name%20talent%20involved%20demands%20it).%20The%20streamer%20has%20so%20many%20subscribers%20all%20over%20the%20world%20that%20it's%20betting%20that%20sooner%20or%20later%20you'll%20open%20the%20app%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20you%20do%2C%20you'll%20be%20fed%20a%20movie%20on%20its%20landing%20page%20and%20hit%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20another%20example%20of%20Netflix's%20strategy%20in%20action.%20As%20a%20movies%20reporter%20whose%20job%20it%20is%20to%20know%20about%20upcoming%20releases%20(and%20who%20regularly%20fields%20countless%20pitches%20from%20publicists%20about%20their%20newest%20titles)%2C%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20that%20the%20teen%20comedy%20%26quot%3BIncoming%26quot%3B%20and%20action%20movie%20%26quot%3BRebel%20Ridge%2C%26quot%3B%20existed%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%2C%20until%20I%20started%20seeing%20them%20on%20my%20timeline%20the%20day%20they%20were%20released.%20Both%20spent%20time%20on%20Netflix's%20coveted%20Netflix%20Top%2010%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Netflix's%20watercooler%20model%20may%20be%20proving%20itself%20a%20cost-saving%20win%2C%20it%20came%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20trial%20and%20error.%20It's%20also%20a%20strategy%20that's%20hard%20to%20duplicate.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20ask%20Apple.%20Its%20Apple%20TV%2B%20service%20is%20finding%20success%20on%20the%20TV%20side%20with%20%26quot%3BTed%20Lasso%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BSeverance%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Morning%20Show%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20it's%20still%20struggling%20to%20become%20a%20destination%20for%20movies%20since%20%26quot%3BCODA%26quot%3B%20won%20best%20picture%20at%20the%20Oscars%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20Apple%20releases%20like%20%26quot%3BNapoleon%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BFly%20Me%20to%20the%20Moon%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Instigators%26quot%3B%20haven't%20drawn%20big%20audiences.%20And%20though%20the%20streamer%20did%20get%20Martin%20Scorsese%20to%20come%20on%20with%20%26qu