nes%20in%20recent%20years%20due%20to%20fatal%20Osprey%20crashes.%20Many%20are%20still%20grappling%20with%20grief%20and%20trying%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20the%20tragedies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20family%20member%20of%20an%20airman%20who%20died%20in%20the%20November%2029%20crash%20in%20Japan%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they%20were%20skeptical%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fair-force%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAir%20Force%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20deploying%20Ospreys%20again%20and%20said%20the%20loved%20ones%20of%20aircrews%20should%20be%20prepared%20for%20the%20worst.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20hearts%20go%20out%20to%20the%20families%20of%20the%20next%20unlucky%20Osprey%20crew%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20family%20member%20said.%20%26quot%3BWords%20cannot%20do%20the%20experience%20justice%2C%20but%20know%20that%20the%20Osprey%20families%20are%20here%20for%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Debris%20believed%20to%20be%20from%20a%20US%20military%20Osprey%20aircraft%20is%20seen%20in%20waters%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Yakushima%20Island.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ac0ecab4912df3ae1864f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDebris%20believed%20to%20be%20from%20a%20US%20military%20Osprey%20aircraft%20is%20seen%20in%20waters%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Yakushima%20Island.%3Cp%3EJapan%20Coast%20Guard%20via%20AP%2C%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20November%2029%20Air%20Force%20Special%20Operations%20Command%20crash%20of%20the%20CV-22%20with%20the%20call%20sign%20Gundam%2022%20claimed%20the%20lives%20of%20Maj.%20Jeffrey%20Hoernemann%3B%20Maj.%20Eric%20Spendlove%3B%20Maj.%20Luke%20Unrath%3B%20Capt.%20Terrell%20Brayman%3B%20Tech.%20Sgt.%20Zachary%20Lavoy%3B%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Jake%20Turnage%3B%20Senior%20Airman%20Brian%20Johnson%3B%20and%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Jake%20Galliher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fdaily-news%2F2024%2F08%2F21%2Fflaw-osprey-gears-was-known-decade-prior-deadly-japan-crash-internal-report-shows.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eafter%20obtaining%20internal%20safety%20documents%20examining%20the%20November%2029%20crash%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20that%20a%20mechanical%20issue%20that%20caused%20the%20incident%20had%20been%20identified%20as%20far%20back%20as%202013%2C%20and%20a%20warning%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20Pentagon%2C%20but%20the%20concerns%20went%20unresolved.%20The%20cause%20of%20the%20Japan%20crash%20was%20determined%20to%20be%20the%20fracturing%20of%20a%20high-speed%20planetary%20pinion%20gear%20in%20the%20aircraft's%20prop%20rotor%20gearbox.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20earlier%20concerns%20brought%20up%20in%20the%20crash%20report%2C%20Conley%20told%20reporters%20that%20he%20did%20not%20believe%20there%20were%20any%20concerns%20from%20a%20manufacturing%20standpoint%20with%20Bell-Boeing%2C%20the%20joint%20venture%20between%20the%20two%20companies%20that%20make%20the%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20Vice%20Adm.%20Carl%20Chebi%2C%20who%20heads%20NAVAIR%2C%20told%20Congress%20in%20June%20that%20he%20did%20not%20expect%20the%20fleet%20to%20be%20fully%20operational%20until%20mid-2025.%20But%20Conley%20said%20his%20Ospreys%20will%20be%20ready%20to%20go%20sooner%20than%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20there's%20certainly%20nothing%20foolproof%2C%20but%20we've%20learned%20a%20lot%20during%20the%20investigation%2C%20and%20both%20Bell%20and%20NAVAIR%2C%20in%20their%20own%20relations%2C%20have%20learned%20a%20lot%2C%20and%20we're%20taking%20what%20we've%20learned%20to%20try%20to%20prevent%20this%20from%20happening%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20Conley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrior%20Air%20Force%20policy%20says%20that%20after%20three%20%26quot%3Bchip%20burn%26quot%3B%20lights%20%E2%80%94%20an%20indicator%20that%20the%20gears%20are%20shedding%20metal%20%E2%80%94%20Osprey%20crews%20should%20%26quot%3Bland%20as%20soon%20as%20practical%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20the%20first%20and%20least%20serious%20of%20three%20landing%20conditions.%20But%20the%20policy%20also%20gives%20pilots%20the%20opportunity%20to%20press%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20airman%20works%20on%20the%20dismantled%20wing%20of%20a%20CV-22%20Osprey%20during%20engine%20maintenance.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c7a69d1aa2ac29ee3386bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22665%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20airman%20works%20on%20the%20dismantled%20wing%20of%20a%20CV-22%20Osprey%20during%20engine%20maintenance.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20photo%2FSenior%20Airman%20Christopher%20Callaway%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Gundam%2022%20crew%20did%20press%20on%20after%20the%20chip%20burn%20lights%20and%20did%20not%20violate%20their%20training.%20Following%20the%20crash%2C%20AFSOC%20changed%20its%20policies%2C%20and%20crews%20are%20now%20advised%20to%20land%20as%20soon%20as%20practical%20after%20a%20single%20chip%20burn%20and%20%26quot%3Bas%20soon%20as%20possible%26quot%3B%20following%20a%20second%20chip%20burn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmber%20Sax%2C%20the%20wife%20of%20Capt.%20John%20Sax%2C%20a%20pilot%20who%20died%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fmarine-corps%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMarine%20Corps%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20Osprey%20when%20it%20crashed%20into%20the%20southern%20California%20desert%20on%20June%208%2C%202022%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20still%20doesn't%20believe%20there%20are%20enough%20public-facing%20solutions%20to%20the%20mechanical%20problems%20that%20have%20plagued%20the%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fear%20many%20surviving%20family%20members%20continue%20to%20have%20is%20that%20the%20failures%20that%20caused%20the%20loss%20of%20their%20loved%20one%20have%20not%20been%20fully%20addressed%20and%20corrected.%20We%20each%20have%20a%20list%20of%20friends%2C%20some%20we%20consider%20family%2C%20who%20continue%20to%20fly%20in%20the%20Osprey%2C%26quot%3B%20Sax%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20thought%20of%2020%20or%20more%2C%20given%20the%20number%20of%20lives%20an%20Osprey%20can%20carry%2C%20haunts%20many%20of%20us%20daily.%20We%20need%20to%20know%20it's%20been%20fixed%2C%20and%20it%20won't%20happen%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConley%20reiterated%20his%20confidence%20in%20the%20steps%20AFSOC%20had%20taken%20to%20address%20the%20issues%20and%20said%2C%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20Gundam%2022%20crash%2C%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20data%20suggests%20it's%20very%20rare.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20be%20blunt%20about%20it%2C%20I%20would%20not%20put%20the%20men%20and%20women%20of%20AFSOC%20back%20in%20the%20plane%20if%20I%20wasn't%20confident%20that%20it%20could%20do%20what%20we%20needed%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Conley%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKonstantin%20Toropin%20contributed%20to%20this%20report.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-air-force-ospreys-redeploy-grounding-japan-crash-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726775415000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ec6828d17aa3c7b2b438a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-air-force-ospreys-redeploy-grounding-japan-crash-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Most%20of%20the%20Air%20Force's%20V-22%20fleet%20has%20returned%20to%20the%20skies%20after%20a%20crash%20last%20y