00%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%227%20people%20stand%20on%20stage%20holding%20a%20giant%20check%20for%20%24750%2C000%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66eb4642d17aa3c7b2b3ff81%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInterstellar%20Lab%20won%20NASA's%20grand%20prize%20for%20its%20project%20designed%20to%20help%20feed%20and%20nourish%20astronaut%20on%20long-duration%20spaceflights.%3Cp%3EKen%20Chamberlain%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENASA%20needs%20a%20better%20way%20to%20nourish%20its%20astronauts%20on%20long-duration%20space%20missions%2C%20like%20to%20Mars.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInterstellar%20Lab%20designed%20a%20sustainable%20farming%20system%20that%20could%20address%20the%20issue.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFor%20its%20efforts%2C%20Interstellar%20Lab%20won%20NASA's%20Deep%20Space%20Food%20Challenge%20and%20took%20home%20%24750%2C000.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdo-astronauts-age-slower-than-people-on-earth-2015-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoing%20to%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20its%20perks%20but%20fresh%2C%20nutritious%20food%20isn't%20one%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENASA's%20Deep%20Space%20Food%20Challenge%2C%20launched%20in%202021%2C%20asked%20teams%20worldwide%20to%20develop%20a%20sustainable%20way%20to%20feed%20and%20nourish%20astronauts%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-invest-mars-pulsed-plasma-rocket-shorten-space-time-travel-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong-duration%20space%20missions%2C%20including%20to%20Mars%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biotech%20company%20Interstellar%20Lab%20beat%20over%20300%20competing%20teams%20to%20receive%20NASA's%20%24750%2C000%20grand%20prize%20in%20August%20for%20its%20project%20NuCLEUS%20(NUtritional%20Closed-Loop%20Eco-Unit%20System).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENuCLEUS%20consists%20of%20a%20series%20of%20cubes%20that%20resemble%20a%20large%20tic-tac-toe%20board.%20The%20cubes%20mostly%20contain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-astronauts-share-successful-harvest-of-fresh-vegetables-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evegetable%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20microgreens%2C%20mushrooms%2C%20or%20insects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224608%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22nine%20white%20cubes%20in%20the%20shape%20of%20a%20human-sized%20tic-tac-toe%20board%20that%20make%20up%20the%20NuCLEUS%20farm%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66eb455ece3009a0fac77dac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223072%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENuCLEUS%20resembles%20a%20life-sized%20tic-tac-toe%20board.%3Cp%3EInterstellar%20Lab%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20Interstellar%20Lab%20has%20tested%2010%20different%20vegetable%20and%20microgreen%20plants%20(including%20Daikon%20radish%2C%20broccoli%2C%20amaranth%2C%20shishito%20peppers%2C%20fenugreek%2C%20and%20onions)%2C%20one%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fafter-asteroid-volcano-nuke-mushrooms-help-humans-survive-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emushroom%20variety%20(oyster)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20one%20insect%20species%20(black%20soldier%20flies)%2C%20with%20plans%20to%20add%20more%20to%20the%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20all%20fresh%20and%20edible%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20flies.%20The%20variety%20isn't%20designed%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronaut-leland-melvin-space-food-taste-good-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eastronauts'%20appetites%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though.%20It's%20for%20their%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20solar%20radiation%2C%20the%20nutritional%20value%20of%20prepackaged%20food%20starts%20to%20degrade%20after%20being%20in%20space%20for%20seven%20to%20eight%20months%2C%20which%20can%20leave%20astronauts%20on%20long-duration%20space%20missions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-signs-eat-more-for-better-energy-performance-dietitian-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeficient%20in%20key%20vitamins%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20minerals%20like%20magnesium%2C%20potassium%2C%20and%20B12%2C%20according%20to%20Barbara%20Belvisi%2C%20Interstellar%20Lab's%20founder%20and%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC8747021%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20these%20nutritional%20gaps%20can%20make%20it%20difficult%20for%20astronauts%20to%20combat%20bone%20loss%2C%20muscle%20atrophy%2C%20cardiovascular%20dysfunction%2C%20and%20the%20other%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-effects-human-body-brain-bones-dna-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ephysiological%20challenges%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20come%20with%20living%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20list%20of%20specific%20nutrients%20that%20NASA%20was%20interested%20in%20growing%20fresh%20food%20to%20cover%20those%20gaps.%20And%20so%20this%20is%20where%20we%20started%2C%26quot%3B%20Belvisi%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20NuCLEUS%20is%20designed%20to%20supplement%20prepackaged%20food%2C%20not%20replace%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20final%20phase%20of%20NASA's%20competition%2C%20NuCLEUS%20produced%20about%2022%20pounds%20of%20plants%20and%20insects%20over%201.5%20months.%20A%20single%20crew%20member%20on%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-havent-we-been-to-mars-yet-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elong-duration%20mission%2C%20like%20to%20Mars%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20would%20require%20about%20661%20pounds%20per%20year%20(or%20about%20four%20times%20that%20amount)%2C%20Belvisi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20the%20version%20tested%20for%20NASA's%20competition%20is%20a%20prototype%20and%20the%20company%20is%20working%20on%20the%20next%20generation%2C%20which%20will%20be%20capable%20of%20producing%20more%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22124beb8d-a781-4b75-bcd8-d97cdd6e2230%5C%22%3EFarming%20in%20space%20with%20AI%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223072%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20person%20in%20a%20white%20jumpsuit%20points%20on%20a%20pad%20attached%20to%20the%209-cube%20NuCLEUS%20farm%20system%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66eb4506ce3009a0fac77d8b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224608%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENuCLEUS%20contains%20nine%20cubes.%20Most%20are%20for%20growing%20food.%20A%20few%20contain%20the%20equipment%20necessary%20to%20keep%20it%20all%20running.%3Cp%3EInterstellar%20Lab%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffirst-time-scientists-have-grown-plants-in-moon-soil-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFarming%20in%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20look%20very%20different%20from%20farming%20on%20Earth.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20NuCLEUS%2C%20AI%20does%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20NuCLEUS%20cube%20is%20a%20contained%20environment.%20The%20software%20that%20controls%20the%20lighting%2C%20humidity%2C%20and%20temperature%20in%20each%20cube%20manipulates%20the%20environment%20to%20provide%20the%20optimal%20growing%20conditions%20for%20each%20plant's%20nutritional%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterstellar%20Lab's%20AI%20collects%20and%20processes%20the%20data%2C%20which%20then%20informs%20the%20software%20on%20how%20it%20can%20improve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20is%20why%20NASA%20liked%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Belvisi%20said%20of%20NuCLEUS.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20because%20there%20is%20this%20smart%20system%20that%20is%20adapting%20itself%2C%20and%20the%20human%20has%20to%20do%20very%20little%20intervention%20compared%20to%20existing%20systems%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20benefit%20is%20that%20NuCLEUS%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-the-plant-chicago-closed-loop-urban-food-production-experiment-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclosed-loop%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20can%20function%20on%20its%20own%2C%20more%20or%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20insects%20eat%20the%20inedible%20portions%20of%20the%20vegetable%20and%20mushroom%20plants.%20The%20flies'%20by-products%20(like%20feces)%20get%20reincorporated%20as%20fertilizer.%20Even%20the%20water%20is%20recycled.%20Most%20of%20the%20waste%20is%20repurposed%20in%20some%20way%2C%20generating%20minimal%20trash%20that%20would%20otherwise%20take%20up%20room%20on%20a%20spaceship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20outside%20resources%20NuCLEUS%20requires%20are%20power%2C%20additional%20water%2C%20and%20time%20from%20the%20crew%2C%20Belvisi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227b0ea8e0-bd11-4fba-9b2d-19f1011e5ac7%5C%22%3EInterstellar%20Lab%20is%20launching%20one%20of%20its%20systems%20into%20space%20next%20year%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224995%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%2215%20members%20of%20interstellar%20lab%20pose%20for%20the%20camera%20while%20standing%20around%20the%209%20white%20cubes%20that%20make%20up%20their%20NuCLEUS%20farm%20project%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66eb448cd17aa3c7b2b3fe42%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223330%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPart%20of%20NASA's%20%24750%2C000%20award%20will%20go%20toward%20paying%20the%20team%20for%20their%20hard%20work.%3Cp%3EInterstellar%20Lab%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20NuCLEUS%20was%20designed%20with%20NASA%20astronauts%20in%20mind%2C%20Belvisi%20said%20that%20Interstellar%20Lab%20is%20also%20working%20with%20private%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterstellar%20Lab%20is%20scheduled%20to%20launch%20one%20of%20its%20NuCLEUS%20systems%20into%20space%20early%20next%20year%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20n