d%20do%20more%20to%20encourage%20their%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImplementation%20of%20these%20steps%20requires%20detailed%20mapping%20of%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20settlements%20and%20topography%2C%20serious%20and%20consistent%20community%20engagement%2C%20and%20collaboration%20with%20environmental%20engineers%20experienced%20in%20high-altitude%20and%20cold-climate%20sanitation.%20There%20should%20be%20a%20phased%20roll-out%20of%20each%20of%20these%20steps%20with%20pilot%20projects%20in%20key%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20decentralised%20approach%20would%20be%20more%20adaptable%20to%20Leh%E2%80%99s%20unique%20geography%20and%20could%20be%20implemented%20more%20quickly%20and%20cost-effectively%20than%20a%20centralised%20system.%20It%20would%20also%20be%20more%20resilient%2C%20as%20a%20problem%20in%20one%20small%20system%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20affect%20the%20entire%20area%E2%80%99s%20sanitation%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Chorol%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20steps%20are%20critical%20given%20how%20groundwater%20is%20primarily%20used%20by%20households%2C%20industries%2C%20hotels%2C%20and%20various%20institutions%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20Leh%20town%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.mongabay.com%2F2024%2F07%2Frapid-urbanisation-and-climate-change-threaten-groundwater-resources-in-ladakh-says-study%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMongabay%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Dr%20Farooq%20Dar%20stated%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhatever%20water%20is%20pumped%20from%20the%20underground%20reserves%2C%20roughly%2093%25%20of%20that%20is%20used%20for%20these%20purposes.%20Ladakh%20is%20also%20shifting%20towards%20self-sufficiency%20in%20the%20food%20and%20crop%20market.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20also%20demands%20huge%20%5Bamounts%20of%5D%20water%2C%20and%20for%20that%2C%20people%20drill%20wells.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20pumped%20groundwater%20is%20nearly%207%25%2C%20used%20